subSubSection.paragraph:
This new species can be distinguished from all other 

Oragua

by the following combination of characters: (
1
) body dark with small pale spots all over dorsal surface; (
2
) shaft of aedeagus short and curved anterodorsally, without apical processes; and (
3
) paraphyses with basal connection of rami membranous and rami about four times longer than connective, broadened apically.
